//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Configuration
//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

top_sse710_r0_aontop_3.xml describes SSE-710 with all possible RTL parameter configuration.

You can use the provided Build_Component script to generate a new
description for a specific SSE-710 configuration. The 'configured' description
has all configuration options resolved.

For more details about Build_Component, see the section 'Using Build_Component'
below.

//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Using Build_Component
//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The Build_Component script can be used to generate a configured IP-XACT file
from the provided component description. Running the scripts results in an IP-XACT component
file that describes SSE-710 with the specific parameters (see Configuration above).

You can run the Build_Component in the directory '/top_sse710_r0_3/top_sse710_r0_aontop_3/ipxact/arm.com/Corstone' with the following command:

../../../../../shared/tools/ipxact/Build_Component <filename.xml> [<uniquifier>] [-config <config_file>]
  
Where: <filename.xml>
         IP-XACT file to base configuration on

       <uniquifier>
         A unique string to potentially append to the configured component filename.

       <config_file>
         A file that contains a list of all the <parameter_name> = <parameter_value> pairs required to build a specific configuration of the component.
         Each name and value pair must be on a different line.
         Use this option if you have saved a configuration from a previous script invocation.
  
Example:

../../../../../shared/tools/ipxact/Build_Component top_sse710_r0_aontop_3.xml configured -config sse710_ipxact_config

The above example will produce a configured IP-XACT file 'top_sse710_r0_aontop_3_configured.xml'.


Notes
----- 

1) You should make sure that the IP-XACT configuration file aligns with the 
   RTL parameter settings when instantiating SSE-710 top-level module.
